package welcome;

public class arrayeven {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int a[]= {1,2,3,4,5};
		
		System.out.println("The even numbers are:");
		for(int i=0;i<a.length;i++) {
			
			if(a[i]%2==0) {
				System.out.println(a[i]);
			}
			
		}
	
		// TODO print the  even and odd

	}

}

DETAILED DESCRIPTION:
this problem `arrayeven` program in Java identifies and prints even numbers from an array. 
It defines an integer array `a` and iterates through its elements using a `for` loop. Within the loop, it checks if each number is even using the modulus operator (`%`) and prints it if true. 
OUTPUT:
The even numbers are:
2
4
